zxr10qos.description: This MIB Module provides Textual Conventions and OBJECT-ID Objects to be used by zxros qos module.

EntryStatus.name: EntryStatus
EntryStatus.description: The row status value of qos configration

qosModuleStart.name: qosModuleStart
qosModuleStart.description: This object indicates if the qos module start or not. 1 start,0 not start.

qosFreeCirIndex.name: qosFreeCirIndex
qosFreeCirIndex.description: The first free cir item index.When a new cir item is created it is used to find a space to save the cir item configration;When deleted its value equals to the index of the cir item deleted, so when a new cir item is created the space can be used again.

qosCbQosPoliceCfgExceedSetValue.description: New packet attribute values for each packets that conforms to the configured Police rate.

qosREDCfgPreValue.name: qosREDCfgPreValue
qosREDCfgPreValue.description: The IP precedence of this entry.

qosREDprecedenceCfgMinThreshold.name: qosREDprecedenceCfgMinThreshold
qosREDprecedenceCfgMinThreshold.description: Minimum threshold in number of packets. When the average queue length reaches this number, WRED begins to drop packets with the specified IP precedence.

qosREDprecedenceCfgMaxThreshold.name: qosREDprecedenceCfgMaxThreshold
qosREDprecedenceCfgMaxThreshold.description: Maximum threshold in number of packets. When the average queue length exceeds this number, WRED drops all packets with the specified IP precedence.

qosREDprecedenceCfgPktDropProb.name: qosREDprecedenceCfgPktDropProb
qosREDprecedenceCfgPktDropProb.description: Denominator for the fraction of packets dropped when the average queue depth is MaxDepthThreshold. For example, if the denominator is 10, one out of every 10 packets is dropped when the average queue is at the MaxDepthThreshold.

qosREDCfgprecedenceRowStatus.name: qosREDCfgprecedenceRowStatus
qosREDCfgprecedenceRowStatus.description: The row status of qos wred configration.

qosREDCfgweightValue.name: qosREDCfgweightValue
qosREDCfgweightValue.description: The decay factor for the queue average calculation. The decay factor is equal to raising 2 to the power of N, where N could be up to 16. The smaller the number, the faster it decays.

qosREDCfgweightRowStatus.name: qosREDCfgweightRowStatus
qosREDCfgweightRowStatus.description: The row status of qos wred weight configration.
